        "content": "<p>How should the following be formatted?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">theorem</span> <span class=\"n\">forget₂_map_associator_hom</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">X</span> <span class=\"n\">Y</span> <span class=\"n\">Z</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">AlgebraCat.</span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span>\n    <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">forget₂</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">AlgebraCat</span> <span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ModuleCat</span> <span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">associator</span> <span class=\"n\">X</span> <span class=\"n\">Y</span> <span class=\"n\">Z</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">hom</span>\n      <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">α_</span>\n        <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">forget₂</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ModuleCat</span> <span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">|&gt;.</span><span class=\"n\">obj</span> <span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n        <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">forget₂</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ModuleCat</span> <span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">|&gt;.</span><span class=\"n\">obj</span> <span class=\"n\">Y</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n        <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">forget₂</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ModuleCat</span> <span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">|&gt;.</span><span class=\"n\">obj</span> <span class=\"n\">Z</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">hom</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">rfl</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/contribute/style.html\">#style</a> suggests that <code>=</code> (as an \"infix operator\") should be on the end of the previous line rather than the start of the next; but I'd argue this makes it harder to separate the LHS and RHS, especially if both contain line wrapping.</p>",
